<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0451</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chilly Weather In Central, Eastern U.S.</HEAD>
<HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Chilly weather dominated the central and eastern United States
today, while the South remained warm and showers lingered in the
Southwest.
   Clear skies and light winds accompanied the sharp dip in
temperatures this morning as the mercury plummeted into the 30s
from the middle and upper Mississippi Valley to the middle and
northern Atlantic Coast, with readings below freezing in northern
New England and upstate New York.
   Temperatures remained in the 70s and lower 80s this morning in
the Gulf Coast region and the deserts of the Southwest.
   Rain developed in the central United States and continued from
Arkansas to northwest Texas today.
   In the Southwest, thunderstorms developed, and one of them
spawned a tornado near Tonopah, Nev., Thursday afternoon, but the
thunderstorms dissipated during the evening. By this morning only
widely scattered light showers remained.
   A few showers and thunderstorms continued in southern Florida,
and widely scattered showers and thunderstorms lingered along the
southern Atlantic Coast and in the lower Great Lakes region.
   Fair skies prevailed across the rest of the nation.
   Today's forecast called for showers from parts of the central
and southern Plateau into the southern Plains, and in southern
Florida. Fog and low clouds were expected to blanket the northern
Pacific Coast.
   Predicted high temperatures: 60s or 70s across much of the
nation; 50s in central Plains, and from the upper Great Lakes
through the central Appalachians to the mid-Atlantic Coast region;
40s from the northeast parts of the Great Lakes through the upper
Ohio Valley into New England; 80s from the California valleys into
central and eastern Oregon, south-central Washington state and
southwest Idaho; and 90s across the desert Southwest.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 24 degrees
at Houlton, Maine, to 84 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 52 fair; Boston 40 fair; Buffalo 43 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 56 fair; Cincinnati 40 foggy; Cleveland 44 cloudy;
Detroit 45 cloudy; Miami 75 fair; New York 49 partly cloudy;
Philadelphia 43 fair; Pittsburgh 40 cloudy; Portland, Maine 32
fair; Washington 44 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 37 fair; Chicago 41 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
60 fair; Denver 37 fair; Des Moines 37 fair; Indianapolis 39 fair;
Kansas City 38 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 36 fair; Nashville 50
cloudy; New Orleans 61 fair; St. Louis 45 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 53 partly cloudy; Anchorage 39 cloudy; Las
Vegas 66 fair; Los Angeles 63 cloudy; Phoenix 80 fair; Salt Lake
City 56 fair; San Diego 65 cloudy; San Francisco 57 partly cloudy;
Seattle 57 foggy.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 partly cloudy; Toronto 39 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
