<HEAD>Gunmen Attack Chile's Honorary Consul</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four gunmen burst into the office of
Chile's honorary consul today, hit him on the head with a pistol
butt and fired a shot into the floor, officials said.
   Istanbul Governor Cahit Bayar said the consul, Mordo Dinar, was
slightly injured.
   Bayar said no group claimed responsibility for the attack at
Dinar's law office, which also serves as the Chilean hononary
consulate.
   But the intruders left banners protesting the government of Gen.
Augusto Pinochet, the governor said. Pinochet lost a referendum
this week he hoped would extend his 15-year-rule until 1997, but he
rejected demands that he step down as president before his term
expires in 1990.
   The semi-official Anatolia news agency quoted witnesses as
saying the gunmen spoke Turkish and the banners were in Turkish and
English.
   Bayar said police were searching for the gunmen.
</TEXT>
