<1ST_LINE>r w PM-LighterRecall     10-07 0202</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Lighter Recall,200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bic Recalling Lighters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bic is recalling its new, regular size
fixed-flame cigarette lighters because some of them may fail to
extinguish, the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission announced
today.
   About 6.5 million of the lighters have been distributed since
they were introduced in July, the agency said.
   No incidents or injuries have been reported involving the
lighters. But the company decided on the recall after determining
that the fire may not go out on 0.04 percent of the lighters, the
commission reported. The problem has been corrected on lighters now
being made, officials said.
   The lighters in question are sold in a plastic pouch or tray and
are labeled ``with fixed flame.'' They can be identified because
they do not have the small wheel used on some lighters to adjust
the flame size.
   Bic Mini fixed flame lighters and Bic regular sized adjustable
lighters, which represent 98 percent of Bic lighters on the market,
are not involved in the recall, the commission said.
   Consumers should stop use of the regular size fixed flame
lighters and return them to the store where purchased for a refund.
Those needing more information can contact the commission at
1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
