<HEAD>Birthday Candles Trigger False Fire Alarm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, British Columbia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Just how much heat do 100
candles generate?
   Apparently enough to set off fire alarms at Richmond Memorial
Hospital, bringing four fire trucks and 16 firefighters to
interrupt a patient's birthday party.
   About 115 family members, friends and fellow patients had
gathered Thursday in this Vancouver suburb to celebrate Katome
Koboyashi's 100th birthday.
   ``They had arranged to wheel her out into the main room at the
same time the family was to wheel in the cake from the other
side,'' said party organizer Anne De Silva.
   Just as Kobayashi and her cake were to meet, the crowd was
startled by the alarms.
   ``It was more confused than anything else,'' De Silva said. ``In
the end, we even forgot to have her blow out the candles.''
   ``We just got there, canceled the alarm and got the heck out,''
said district fire chief Harry Beetstra. ``We didn't want to
disturb the party.''
