<2ND_LINE>AM-Bulgaria-Train Crash,0183</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Die In Rail Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three railway employees were killed and
at least six people were seriously injured when an express train
ran off the track, the official BTA news agency said Friday.
   BTA said seven cars and the engine of the train, running between
the capital, Sofia, and the Black Sea resort of Varna, derailed as
the train entered a local station about 50 miles northeast of Sofia.
   The accident Thursday night was due to a ``wrongly prepared
route,'' BTA said without further explanation.
   Six people were hospitalized in serious condition in the city of
Pleven, BTA said. It did not say how many people were in the train
that derailed.
   The accident came a week after a government commission blamed
negligence and gross violations of discipline for summer plane and
train crashes in which 39 people died.
   Four top transportation officials were fired last week.
   On Aug. 2, a plane crash at Sofia's airport killed 29 people. A
train crash just outside Sofia on Sept. 14 killed 10 people.
</TEXT>
