<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Turkey-Chile     10-07 0189</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Turkey-Chile,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chile's Honorary Consul Injured By Gunmen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four Turkish-speaking gunmen entered the
office of Chile's hononary consul Friday, hit him with a pistol
butt and fired a shot into the floor, officials reported.
   Mordo Dinar, Chile's honorary consul in Istanbul since 1953,
suffered a minor head injury in the attack at his law office,
according to Istanbul Gov. Cahit Bayar.Bayar said no group claimed
responsibility.
   The semi-official Anatolia news agency quoted witnesses as
saying the gunmen left behind banners saying, ``Down with
Pinochet!'' referring to Chilean President Augusto Pinochet and his
military government.
   Anatolia also reported Dinar expressed support for the results
of the Chilean referendum Wednesday when the voters rejected a
proposal that Pinochet, who also is commander of the army, serve as
president until 1997.
   The agency quoted Dinar as saying, ``I hoisted the Chilean flag
at the building today for the first time in 15 years to join the
Chilean people celebrating the results of the referendum, and will
keep it there.''
   Pinochet led the military coup in September 1973 that ousted the
elected government of Marxist President Salvador Allende.
