<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   DAN QUAYLE, shrugging off new Democratic campaign commercials
aimed at raising doubts about his fitness for high office: ``We can
stand the heat. We're going to stay in the kitchen. George Bush is
going to be the next president of the United States. The voters
will vote for him.''
   
   LLOYD BENTSEN, breaking down into laughter while scoffing at
Republican assertions that Quayle did well in the vice presidential
debate: ``I was reading the paper this morning where George Bush
said he thought won that, and yet every ... I'm sorry.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, unaware he is speaking at an auto parts plant
that is foreign-owned, blasting Quayle's debate-night assertion
that he welcomed foreign investment in the United States: ``If
anyone asks you what's at stake in this election, just remind them
of that moment in the debate Wednesday night when Sen. Quayle said
he's happy that foriegn owners are buying up America.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, accusing Dukakis of taking a soft approach to crime
and calling the Massachusetts criminal justice system out of whack:
``(It is) a `Twilight Zone' world where prisoners' right to privacy
had more weight than the citizens' right to safety.''
