<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--AIDS Bite,0143</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>AIDS Inmate Gets 15 Years for Biting Guard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A prisoner carrying the AIDS virus received
a 15-year prison sentence Friday for biting a guard who later
tested negative for the deadly disease.
   Circuit Judge Henry W. Blizzard also sentenced Adam Brock to 10
years for assaulting guards with a padlock.
   The additional sentences were added to Brock's 13-year sentence
for robbery. He had served all but two years of the robbery
sentence.
   Limestone County District Attorney Jimmy Fry said he will pursue
attempted murder charges against any other AIDS inmate who attacks
a guard by biting. He said Brock ``used his mouth as a deadly
weapon.''
   Inmates with acquired immune deficiency syndrome have been
segregated from other prisoners at the Limestone County
Correctional Facility in Capshaw. The AIDS unit holds 117 prisoners.
