<HEAD>Grandson of Former Texas Coach Pleads Guilty To Document Theft</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The grandson of former University of Texas
football coach Darrell Royal has pleaded guilty to stealing an
historic Albert Einstein manuscript from a campus display.
   Samuel K. Royal, 19, pleaded guilty Wednesday to theft charges,
and sentencing was set for Oct. 28.
   He faces a maximum of 10 years in prison and $5,000 fine, but
prosecutors recommended a 5-year deferred sentence, 30 days in
jail, 100 hours of public service, and rehabilitation classes.
   Royal was arrested in April when police found the handwritten
page of mathematical notes in his bedroom closet. The manuscript
had been missing about six days from a locked case in the
university's Flawn Academic Center, police said.
   Darrell Royal, his grandfather, was UT football coach from 1957
to 1976 and is a special assistant to UT president William
Cunningham.
