   The Coniston Partners investment group has
proposed a friendly $1.13 billion takeover of foods giant TW
Services Inc. but suggested it might turn hostile if the offer is
rejected.
   The proposal, which would pay $28 in cash for each of the 39.27
million TW shares Coniston does not already own, was announced
Thursday.
