   The Senate has seized one of the most popular
issues of the presidential campaign and by 94-0 approved a tax
exemption for interest on U.S. savings bonds that are used to
finance a college education.
   The vote Thursday on an amendment to the tax-overhaul bill was
sponsored by Sen. Edward M. Kennedy, D-Mass., who described it as
