who fear it may discourage foreign investment in the already
depressed London stock market.
   The government said Thursday it acted to defend the free market
against a cartel, the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries, to which Kuwait belongs.
   British Petroleum is Britain's largest company, and the Persian
Gulf nation of Kuwait is its biggest shareholder.
</TEXT>
