request by Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. to disqualify the judge
presiding over the government's fraud case against the Wall Street
firm.
   The U.S. 2nd Circuit Court of Appeals in Manhattan said Thursday
in a written ruling that the move by attorneys for Drexel and other
defendants was premature because U.S. District Judge Milton Pollack
had not yet ruled on their motion to remove him from the case.
