<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kroger Co. will lay off about 300 employees at
its headquarters as part of a corporate restructuring aimed at
thwarting unwelcome takeover offers.
   The layoffs announced Thursday ``basically cover everything from
vice president to the secretary level,'' spokesman Paul Bernish
said.
   The nation's largest supermarket operator said the layoffs and
elimination of associated costs will save the company at least $13
million a year.
   Kroger is the object of an unsolicited $5.03 billion buyout
offer from the New York investment firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &
