<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States cannot afford to stop
soon-to-expire steel import quota agreements with Japan, the
European Community and other nations, a study partly sponsored by
the steel industry says.
   The conditions that led to the import barriers in 1984 _
pervasive intervention by foreign governments to help their
steelmakers compete in world markets _ have not changed, according
to the study by three Washington-based attorneys and an economist.
