<TEXT>
   A fraud indictment of a Florida citrus
company is the first growing out of a 22-month nationwide
investigation of illegal citrus practices involving hundreds of
millions of dollars, federal officials say.
   Brad Knutter, supervisor of the the Tampa U.S. Customs fraud
group coordinating the investigation, said Thursday that
``Operation Orange Squeeze'' was not confined to Florida,
indicating that others might be implicated.
