<HEAD>Apple Computer Executive Announces Resignation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CUPERTINO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Delbert W. Yocam, a 10-year veteran of
Apple Computer Inc., said Friday he will leave the firm in November
1989.
   Yocam will continue to serve as president of Apple's Pacific
division until his departure, but the education division that he
has headed will be moved into the Apple USA division, Apple said.
   Yocam is one of the industry's ``finest executives,'' said John
Sculley, Apple's chairman and chief executive.
   Apple also announced a variety of other organizational changes,
including the creation of a separate Apple USA marketing group,
encompassing three separate U.S. marketing organizations and the
Marketing Communications group.
