<1ST_LINE>r f AM-ICSpinoff     10-07 0245</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-IC Spinoff,0254</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>IC Files with SEC to Spin Off Illinois Central Railroad</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   IC Industries Inc. on Friday filed a registration
statement with the Securities and Exchange Commission required for
the spinoff of the Illinois Central Railroad.
   The parent company said it expects to distribute approximately
21 million shares of Illinois Central common stock to shareholders
by the end of the year, after a favorable ruling by the Interstate
Commerce Commission last week.
   Under the proposed plan, IC Industries shareholders willl
receive one share of Illinois Central common stock for each five
shares of IC Industries common stock they hold.
   Application is being made to have the new Illinois Central
common stock listed on the New York Stock Exchange, IC said in a
statement.
   IC Industries had earlier obtained a ruling from the Internal
Revenue Service that the stock dividend will be tax-free to its
shareholders.
   Before the distribution, IC Industries will contribute to the
railroad $180 million in cash and forgiveness of net advances, plus
$25 million in real estate.
   The parent company has been in the process of spinning off the
railroad to its shareholders since early this year.
   With the spinoff of the railroad, IC Industries will change its
name to Whitman Corp., as previously announced, effective Dec. 1.
Its primary operating companies will then be Pet Inc., a specialty
foods company; Pepsi-Cola General Bottlers; muffler specialist
Midas International Inc.; and Hussman Corp., a manufacturer of
food-service equipment.
</TEXT>
